title: OPENING OF THE FIRST CHLOE MAISON, 253 RUE SAINT HONORE PARIS
txt_content: If you are having difficulties viewing this message, click here. OPENING OF THE FIRST CHLOE MAISON, 253 RUE SAINT HONORE PARIS On December 20th, Chloé inaugurated the first Chloé Maison at 253 rue Saint-Honoré in Paris. Creative Director, Clare Waight Keller, collaborated with architect Joseph Dirand to come up with the new, airy design, which reflects the 'free and modern' Chloé woman and creates a welcoming atmosphere. The boutique showcases French workmanship and presents the ready-to-wear collections along with shoes, accessories and fragrances. Chloé Boutique Saint-Honoré 253 rue Saint-Honoré 75001 Paris Tel. +33 (0)1 55 04 03 30 Opening hours: From Monday to Saturday 11am til 7.30pm To celebrate its opening, a limited edition of the 'Alice' bag in just 30 pieces, numbered and engraved, will be exclusively available at the Maison Chloé, 253 Saint-Honoré. You are receiving this newsletter following a registration in Chloé boutique or on the chloe.com website. To learn about how we use your personal information, please click here to read our privacy policy. You may unsubscribe from Chloé newsletter by clicking here. title: Spring 2013 Collection: Now available in boutique
txt_content: If you are having difficulties viewing this message, click here. The Spring 2013 Collection Clare Waight Keller, Chloé Creative Director, introducing the Spring 2013 Collection “This season I thought about the Chloé girl with a very Bohemian spirit, although there is still a sharp modernity to the silhouette, I used a fuller volume which keeps it more feminine. She is a traveler. She mixes her influences. There is an irreverent mood, in the layering of folk blouses with safari cotton cropped pants, military pocket georgette dungaree’s and lace inserted shirts. Colors are in vibrant, mineral shades, punched with dusty tangerine neon, coral and grounded with vintage whites. There is a touch of the late seventies in the "New Romantic" softness but I love it blended with a sharpness from the 80s and tapered tailoring “. The Spring collection also includes an exclusive version of the Alice along with two new handbags lines Vanessa and Sennen. This collection is now available at Chloé boutiques and at authorized retailers. More on chloe.com... More on facebook.com... title: The Chloé Alphabet
txt_content: If you are having difficulties viewing this message, click here. The 26 letters of “The Chloé Alphabet” collectively form a mosaic, bringing to life the inspirations of the Maison since its creation, through films, documentaries and previously unseen archive imagery, each letter telling a fragment of the story: www.chloe.com/alphabet . We sign it off with a ‘X’ (Kiss) - a specially commissioned track “I follow you (Melo’sChloé Christmas Kiss Mix)” by Parisian, pop singer Melody Prochet. For all those that have created, shared, designed, worn and loved Chloé, this is for you. You can now invite a friend to share this journey: type their name and email and they will receive a unique version of the Chloé heritage, following the letters that make up their name. title: Winter 2012/2013 Shoes Collection: Now available
txt_content: If you are having difficulties viewing this message, click here. Winter 2012/2013 Shoes Collection The creative energy of this winter season is based on the stimulating and playful contradiction between a typical casual and carefree London way-of-life and a more sophisticated Parisian elegance. The new collection of Carol shoes reflects this intriguing blend of influences and polishes every silhouette of the Fall/Winter 2012 show. In delicate leather or suede, Carol is available in ten colors for infinite variations, in keeping with the extraordinary richness of the ready-to-wear colour palette. A subtle ankle strap accentuates the femininity of the instep whilst the heel, very graphic in 2 or 4 inches, ensures a slender and confident walk. This new collection is now available at Chloé boutiques and at authorized retailers. More on chloe.com... More on facebook.com...
